%I A394794 #4 May 10 2026 15:08:14
%S A394794 1,2,16,28672
%N A394794 Number of 180-degree rotationally symmetric reduced Latin squares of order 2n.
%C A394794 The layout for the board game Kamisado is a Latin square (although not reduced) with this symmetry, so that the board looks the same to both players (see linked StackExchange post). The Cayley tables for elementary abelian groups of order 2^n have this symmetry, and also appear to maximize the number of stable matchings (see A005154).
%H A394794 Bennett Gardiner, <a href="https://math.stackexchange.com/questions/534531/how-many-latin-squares-are-there-with-the-following-restrictions">How many Latin squares are there with the following restrictions?</a>, MathStackExchange.
%H A394794 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kamisado">Kamisado</a>
%e A394794 not also horizontally symmetric (rows 3-6)
%e A394794   1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8
%e A394794   2 1 4 3 6 5 8 7
%e A394794   3 4 1 2 8 7 5 6
%e A394794   4 3 2 1 7 8 6 5
%e A394794   5 6 8 7 1 2 3 4
%e A394794   6 5 7 8 2 1 4 3
%e A394794   7 8 5 6 3 4 1 2
%e A394794   8 7 6 5 4 3 2 1
